text.tspan: Voltage Ranges:
Adjust for maximum resolution.
+/-160V requires a 10Mohm series resistor
present at the input
Chan 1 can acquire data from
any of the 7 analog inputs (CH1,
CH2,CH3,MIC,SEN,CAP,AN8)
A ) Timebase
Total Duration for which to acquire data. Up to 100mS
width can be specified using the dial.
Use the Scroll wheel of your mouse to easily change it.
C ) Sine Fit/ Square Fit
Fit the data acquired by channels against the chosen
fitting function. Two channels can be chosen for fitting.
Sine fitting involves four parameters : Amplitude,
Frequency, Phase , and Offset.
The results are displayed in the bottom toolbar, and
if two channels were selected, the phase difference is
displayed in brackets
D ) X-Y Mode
Plot Lissajous Figures . The first selection box chooses
'the data for the X-Axis, and the second is for the Y-Axis.
The VIEW button opens the XY plot in a new window.
E) Save Data
Opens the raw data in a spreadsheet. You may save the
acquired data either in CSV format, or as an image.
B ) Trigger
Wait till the input value reaches the specified voltage
level before starting acquisition. This results in periodic
waveforms appearing stationary.
CrossHairs:
Click anywhere on the plot to activate crosshairs.
The time coordinate and the corresponding voltage
values will be displayed in the plot title. Refresh rate
of the scope window is also shown
Channels:
Up to 4 Analog inputs can be simultaneously
Digitized. Click the Checkboxes to select as required
